article.title: On Booth lemniscate of starlike functions

multiple_choice_question.text: Figure 1 depicts the boundary curve of D(α) for a specific value of α. Which shape best describes this boundary curve?
The formula (1.2) defines a one-parameter family of functions, Fa(z). What is the coefficient of z^5 in the series expansion of Fa(z)?
Formula (1.8) defines the class of functions BS(α). What mathematical concept does the symbol "<" represent in this definition?
Formula (2.6) provides an upper bound for the absolute value of the coefficient a_n for functions in the class BS(α). What is the condition on α for this estimate to hold?
